Dear Suleyman Demirel University students! 

We understand that it is very important to continue our mission of searching 
for high-quality education during this transitional period. However, the crisis 
does not eliminate the need to plan for the future. 
The main task that everyone faces today is to get a decent education in their 
chosen specialty and become a professional in their field. Due to the epidemic 
situation in the country, we must conduct the educational process in both 
offline and online formats. Despite all the difficulties, you must continue to 
move towards your goal in a clear direction that leads you to the best future. 
Today it is so important to comply with all sanitary standards that have 
already become a crucial part of everyday life, as well as to make a right 
choice on vaccination playing a significant role for your health. The well-being 
of every student is important to us. 
I wish you great

success! 

Best regards, 
SDU Rector 
Alimzhan IGENBAYEV

I.ABOUT 
THE UNIVERSITY

14

Suleyman Demirel University (hereafter - SDU) is a private university institution 
established on a not- for- profit basis and the ownership is vested in a Trust. SDU 
has  strongly  stated  ambitions  to  develop  leading  edge  international  education 
and  to  provide  graduates  with  skills  and  mobility  relevant  to  the  global  economy. 
The  University  has  created  conditions  for  ensuring  the  availability  and  quality  of 
education that meets the requirements of international and national legislation, for 
continuous training of the teaching staff, and impro

ving the efficiency of University 
management.  The  teaching  staff  of  the  University  carries  out  research  in  various 
fields  of  knowledge.  The  activities  of  the  SDU  are  aimed  at  the  development  and 
implementation of educational, research and scientific programs in such a way as 
to  provide  students  with  all  the  necessary  skills  for  both  professional  growth  and 
personal  development.  Respect  for  the  intellectual  potential  and  dignity  of  the 
student as an individual is paramount.

There are 4 faculties in SDU: SDU Business School, Faculty of Engineering and 
Natural Sciences, Faculty of Education and Humanities, Faculty of Law and Social 
Sciences, including Centre for Multidisciplinary Education.

PAYMENTS 

Financial Matters

All payments are accepted only via Bank or thought online non-cash transactions. 
There are several ways to do it: bank transactions, homebank or kaspi.kz applications, 
or  throught  website  online  payment.  Commissions  differ  depending  on  the  way  of 
payment and individual Bank terms. Kazakhstani students’ payments are accepted 
in  KZT,  and  all  international  students  are  paying  in  USD  according  to  the  charged 
amount which is indicated in the portal of the University. Payment day is the day when 
the money went to the university account, not the day when money is sent. Usually, 
it is the next business day after the payment is completed, except payments made 
ab

road. If money is sent from abroad then it takes longer (needs to be clarified from 
the  country).  The  tuition  fee  is  transferred  to  MYSDU  portal  in  two  days  after  the 
payment operation.

DISCOUNTS 

To promote opportunities for talented students, the University presents a range 
of  discounts.  Please  take  in  consideration  that  discounts  are  given  only  for  main 
tuition (240 ECTS for bachelor) and are not applicable for extracurricular educational 
payments  or  services  like  retakes,  upgrades,  language  courses,  staying  at  student 
houses etc.

You  can  check  the  registration  dates  for  spring/summer  semester  on  the 

website. Each student has got its own system calendar on the portal. 

Course Registration 

Each student is required to go through a course registration process on MYSDU 
portal. Deadlines for the course registrations are outlined in an Academic Calendar 
which  is  located  in  MYSDU  portal  and  SDU  website.  Every  semester  a  student 
takes between 20-40 ECTS credits, it is recommended to take 30 ECTS credits. Pre-
requisite courses are identified prior to the enrollment process. Faculties/School are/
is responsible for preparing a required list of the prerequisites and the deadlines for 
them. Prerequisites incur a charge. The number of ECTS credits should not

exceed

 HOW TO REGISTER ONLINE FOR SDU COURSES?

19

Every SDU University Student has access to its own Student Portal.
Enter your ID, password (is the same as your ID)and press Log in.

Note: Password is the same as your ID!
Change password as soon as possible to protect your Personal Information!
(Student Portal- personal Info- Change password)

MY SDU Portal 

MYSDU portal is Suleyman Demirel student information system, and is the system 
of record for course enrollments. MYSDU portal is used to maintain student records, 
manage course enrollment, and schedule classes. Using the MYSDU Portal, students 
can access information about their academic program, enroll in classes, view course 
history, view their student accounts and update their personal information. Please 
note  that  academic  credit  will  not  be  given  for  coursework  unless  an  enrollment 
record exists in MYSDU PORTAL. 

Login & Password 

MYSDU portal login and password are sent to the student email. If t

he password 

is blocked there are two ways you to make an inquiry: 

1. Send a scan of student ID card to SSC@sdu.edu.kz. The subject line of the 

email should be “MYSDU portal password”. 

2.  Send  a  request  via  https://helpdesk.sdu.edu.kz.  Student  account  (Google, 
WiFi) menu My Profile Key information about the student is provided in the MYSDU 
portal. It is essential to update the information in case of any changes. Changes are 
made only after advisor’s approval. Personal information is strictly confidential and 
only SSC experts and academic advisors are able to access it in the MYSDU portal. 

To  change  the  name/surname  for  informed  reasons,  the  student  must  send  a 

written application and a copy of the original document to SSC@sdu.edu.kz.

however. Foreign exchange programs provide students with an opportunity to study 
in a different country and environment experiencing the history and culture of another 
country. To be eligible for the academic mobility program, students need to:

Passport and Visa 

The  passport  registration  procedure  for  international  student  who  arrived  to 
study  at  the  SDU:  After  crossing  the  customs  border  at  Almaty  airport  or  custom 
control at the borders of Kazakhstan, a student must visit the International Relations 
Office (E110) within 1 working day to submit all necessary documents to the Visa 
Coordinator or his assistant. 
Necessary documents:
 → passport; 
 → migration card given by the Officers from the Customs. 
Students arriving on a student visa receive a notification from the Migration Office 
within 1 working day. Students arriving without a student visa will be registered within 
2 working days. In case of violation of the deadlines, non-compliance with legality 
and the standards of applying to Visa Coordinator or his assistant, the student warns 
that in case of repeated violations the student is sent to the disciplinary

council, and 
by decision of the council, the student is expelled from the university. In accordance 
with  the  law  of  the  Republic  of  Kazakhstan,  and  Article  517  of  the  Administrative 
Code of the Republic of Kazakhstan, students, who violated the period of stay, are 
fined from 15 to 20 MCI, which will be fully paid by the student, as well as arrest up to 
10 days and deportation are possible.
